./sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Zc_1775694627.log:583:./CHANGELOG.md:6:- Added daemon-local `ollama_health()` dual-socket reporting for ports `11434` and `11435`, including per-instance loaded models and measured probe latency.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Zc_1775694627.log:634:./specs/t-010@20260408t223256za-spec.md:5:The live daemon has direct Ollama invocation and basic low-level health helpers, but it does not yet expose one daemon-local helper that summarizes both configured Ollama sockets. This subtask needs a synchronous `ollama_health()` helper in the daemon that queries ports `11434` and `11435` and returns stable per-instance status, loaded model names, and measured response latency for later `/status` and `/local` integration.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Zc_1775694627.log:635:./specs/t-010@20260408t223256za-spec.md:9:- Add a daemon-local `ollama_health()` helper in `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py`.
