./sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Zc_1775694627.log:644:./specs/t-010@20260408t223256za-spec.md:27:1. `cypherclaw_daemon.ollama_health()` returns a stable JSON-serializable summary for both Ollama sockets `11434` and `11435`.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Zc_1775694627.log:649:./specs/t-010@20260408t223256zb-spec.md:5:`ollama_health()` was added in T-010a but is not yet surfaced anywhere the operator can see it. The `/status` Telegram command shows only conversation count, running tasks, schedules, and artifacts — no Ollama instance health. The half-hour heartbeat payload similarly omits Ollama status. Operators have no way to see whether local LLM instances are alive without SSH.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Zc_1775694627.log:650:./specs/t-010@20260408t223256zb-spec.md:9:1. **`/status` command** — Call `ollama_health()` inside `handle_builtin` for the `/status` branch. Pass the result into `CypherClawArt.status_display()` (add an optional `ollama` keyword parameter) so the display includes per-socket health, loaded models, and latency.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Zc_1775694627.log:651:./specs/t-010@20260408t223256zb-spec.md:11:2. **Heartbeat payload** — Call `ollama_health()` inside `format_half_hour_heartbeat()` and add an `"ollama"` key to the returned payload dict. Also append a one-line Ollama summary to the heartbeat text.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Zc_1775694627.log:653:./specs/t-010@20260408t223256zb-spec.md:15:4. **Integration test** — Test that `/status` output includes Ollama health text when `ollama_health()` returns healthy/unhealthy instances, and that the heartbeat payload contains the `"ollama"` key.
