./sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Za_1775692978.log:1823:./sdp/verification/t-007@20260408t223256z-verify.md:17:1. **Unhealthy Ollama excluded from candidate list** — `QuotaMonitor._runtime_unavailable_agents()` calls `_refresh_local_provider_status()` on every `get_available_agents()` invocation. When `ollama_health.check_health()` returns `False` for all configured ports, the local provider is blocked and all agents mapped to it are added to the `blocked` set. These are excluded before both the healthy/warn filter and the fallback max-headroom selection.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Za_1775692978.log:1825:./sdp/verification/t-007@20260408t223256z-verify.md:29:- All cloud providers also quota-paused AND Ollama unhealthy: `get_available_agents` returns `[]`, `_eligible_agents` returns `[]`, `select` raises `ValueError("no agents available for selection")` — correct escalation behavior.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Za_1775692978.log:1827:./sdp/verification/t-007@20260408t223256z-verify.md:34:**Test coverage**: Two new targeted tests cover exclusion, fallback, and recovery paths at both the `QuotaMonitor` and `AgentSelector` levels. The `autouse` `_healthy_ollama` fixture correctly protects pre-existing tests from the new live health check.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Za_1775692978.log:1830:./sdp/verification/t-007@20260408t223256z-verify.md:44:No security concerns. The `importlib.import_module("agent_selector")` call inside `_local_provider_ports` reuses an already-imported module from the same path — no new import-path attack surface beyond what existed before. No secrets, credentials, or user-controlled input flows into health check calls. `ollama_health.check_health(port)` takes an integer port, not a URL derived from external input.
