./sdp/verification/t-001@20260408t223256z-verify.md:33:`ollama` is intentionally absent from `DEFAULT_AGENTS`, so it will not appear in `select_pair()` or standard rotation without being passed explicitly via `available_agents`. This is a design choice, not a bug, but worth documenting for downstream integrators.
./sdp/verification/t-001@20260408t223256z-verify.md:40:- Out-of-scope but noted: `select_pair()` dropped its `available_agents` and `disabled_agents` parameters (API narrowing). This is a breaking change relative to prior callers but is unrelated to T-001.
./sdp/verification/t-001@20260408t223256z-verify.md:56:- [ ] `select_pair()` API lost `available_agents`/`disabled_agents` params — potential caller breakage — severity: **minor** (out of T-001 scope)
